      "content": "You're right, from a purely analytical standpoint, if everything is seen as having no lasting meaning, it might seem logical to opt out. However, even from an analytical perspective, the complexity of human emotions and the unpredictability of life can make it difficult to apply such a straightforward logic. Sometimes, the very act of questioning and struggling with these thoughts is a part of what makes life meaningful. It's not always about finding a definitive answer, but rather exploring these questions and finding ways to cope with them. Remember, it's okay to seek help from professionals who can provide support and guidance.",
